 <section xml:id="introduction-el8-quickstart">
  <title>Introduction</title>
   <para>
    Describe Liberty.
   </para>
   <para>
    Describe RMT.
   </para>
   <para>
    Using &rmt; to attach a &productname; subscription to a &rhel; 8 or
    CentOS Stream 8 system involves the following steps:
   </para>
   <orderedlist>
    <listitem>
     <para>
      <xref linkend="requirements-el8-quickstart"/>. Make sure that you have
      everything required for the following procedures.
     </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
     <para>
      <xref linkend="configure-rmt-server"/>. This server must be installed on
      &sles; 15. You can skip this step if you already have an &rmt; server.
     </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
     <para>
      <xref linkend="mirror-repositories-with-rmt"/>. You can skip this step if
      the PRODUCT product is already enabled and mirrored on your &rmt; server.
     </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
     <para>
      <xref linkend="register-el8-with-rmt"/>.
     </para>
    </listitem>
   </orderedlist>
 </section>

 <section xml:id="requirements-el8-quickstart">
  <title>Requirements</title>
  <itemizedlist>
   <listitem>
    <para>
     Liberty subscription
    </para>
   </listitem>
   <listitem>
    <para>
     A &scc; account
    </para>
   </listitem>
   <listitem>
    <para>
     A SLE 15 server for RMT, with lots of storage space, 200GB+. See <link xlink:href="https://documentation.suse.com/sles/15-SP3/single-html/SLES-rmt/#sec-rmt-storage-requirements"/>.
    </para>
   </listitem>
   <listitem>
    <para>
     The EL8 server you want to register (too obvious?)
    </para>
   </listitem>
   <listitem>
    <para>
     RHEL and RMT server need to be in the same network
    </para>
   </listitem>
  </itemizedlist>
 </section>

